hoc2015_reinfFeedbackMsg: You can press the "{backButton}" button to go back to playing your game.
hoc2015_move_right_instructions: "We need that scrap metal. BB-8, can you get it?"
hoc2015_move_right_down_instructions: "We need more scrap metal. Can you get all the metal in this area?"
hoc2015_move_finale_instructions: "We need 4 more pieces of metal. Can you find them?"
hoc2015_event_two_items_instructions: "R2-D2, I need you to get a critical message to the Rebel Pilots."
hoc2015_event_two_items_instructions2: Make R2-D2 move when you use the arrow keys.
hoc2015_event_four_items_instructions: "Get to all of the Rebel Pilots as quickly as you can."
hoc2015_score_instructions2: Let's add points. Add 100 points when R2-D2 gets each Rebel Pilot.
hoc2015_win_lose_instructions2: Add 100 points when R2-D2 gets the Rebel Pilot.  Remove 100 points when he gets a Stormtrooper.  Now, avoid the Stormtroopers and get all the Rebel Pilots!
hoc2015_add_characters_instructions: "I'm seeing signs of increased activity on this planet."
hoc2015_add_characters_instructions2: Add three Puffer Pigs to the planet. Then, go get them.
hoc2015_chain_characters_instructions2: Can you make two Mouse Droids appear every time R2-D2 gets one Mouse Droid?  Get 20 Mouse Droids and score 2000 points.
hoc2015_chain_characters2_instructions2: When you get a Tauntaun, two Mynocks appear. Can you make two Mouse Droids appear when you get a Mynock? Then, get them all.
hoc2015_change_setting_instructions2: Use the new commands to change the map and speed.  Then, get the Rebel Pilots.
hoc2015_event_free_instructions2: You have all the tools you need now to create your own level. Feel free to explore and play with all the different Commands and Events. When you're done, press the Finish button to continue.

failedAvoidHazard: "Uh oh, a Bandit got you!  Try again."
failedHasAllGoals: "Try again, BB-8.  You can get it."
failedTwoItemsTimeout: You need to get the Rebel Pilots before time runs out. To move, put the goUp and goDown commands inside the whenUp and whenDown functions. Then, press and hold the arrow keys on your keyboard (or screen) to move quickly.
failedFourItemsTimeout: To pass this level, you'll need to put goLeft, goRight, goUp and goDown into the right functions. If your code looks correct, but you can't get there fast enough, try pressing and holding the arrow keys on your keyboard (or screen).
failedScoreTimeout: Try to reach all the Rebel Pilots before time runs out. To move faster, press and hold the arrow keys on your keyboard (or screen).
failedScoreScore: You got the Rebel Pilots, but you still don't have enough points to pass the level. Use the addPoints command to add 100 points when you get a Rebel Pilot.
failedScoreGoals: You used the addPoints command, but not in the right place. Can you put it inside the whenGetRebelPilot function so R2-D2 can't get points until he gets a Rebel Pilot?
failedWinLoseTimeout: Try to reach all the Rebel Pilots before time runs out. To move faster, press and hold the arrow keys on your keyboard (or screen).
failedWinLoseScore: You got the Rebel Pilots, but you still don't have enough points to pass the level. Use the addPoints command to add 100 points when you get a Rebel Pilot. Use removePoints to subtract 100 when you touch a Stormtrooper. Avoid the Stormtroopers!
failedWinLoseGoals: You used the addPoints command, but not in the right place. Can you make it so that the command is only called when you get the Rebel Pilot? Also, remove points when you touch the Stormtrooper.
failedAddCharactersTimeout: Use three addCharacter commands at the top of your program to add Puffer Pigs when you hit run. Now go get them.
failedChainCharactersTimeout: You need to get 20 Mouse Droids. They move fast. Try pressing and holding the keys on your keyboard (or screen) to chase them.
failedChainCharactersScore: You got the Mouse Droids, but you don't have enough points to move to the next level. Make sure you add 100 points to your score every time you get a Mouse Droid.
failedChainCharactersItems: You used the addPoints command, but not in the right place.  Can you make it so that the command is only called when you get the Mouse Droids?
failedChainCharacters2Timeout: You need to get eight Mouse Droids. Can you make two (or more) of them appear every time you get a Mynock?
failedChangeSettingTimeout: Get three Rebel Pilots to move on.
failedChangeSettingSettings: Make the level your own. To pass this level, you need to change the map and set your speed.
